abhisamaya







    abhisamaya: 


'truth-realization', 
 is the full and direct grasp of the Four Noble Truths by the Stream-winner (Sotāpanna; 
s. ariya-puggala). 

In the Com. the term is represented by 'penetration' (pativedha, q.v.). 
Frequently occurring as dhammābhisamaya, 'realization of the doctrine' 

Cf. S. XIII (Abhisamaya Samyutta) and Pts.M. (Abhisamaya Kathā).

