domanassa


lit. 'sad-mindedness', grief,  
i.e. mentally painful feeling (cetasika-vedanā), is one of the 5 
feelings (vedanā) and one of the 22 faculties (indriya).  
According to the Abhidhamma, grief is always associated with antipathy and 
grudge, and therefore karmically unwholesome (akusala) Cf. Tab. I. 
