gati







gati 


 (lit. 'going'): 'course of existence', destiny, destination.  
"There are 5 courses of existence: hell, animal kingdom, ghost realm, human 
world, heavenly world" (D. 33; A. XI, 68).  
Of these, the first 3 count as woeful courses (duggati, s. apāya), the 
latter 2 as happy courses (sugati).

