kiñcana







kiñcana


'something', i.e. something evil that sticks or adheres to character.  
'Evil appendant', is a name for the 3 unwholesome roots (mūla).


"There are 3 appendants: greed (lobha) is an appendant, hate (dosa)
is an appendant, delusion (moha) is an appendant" (D. 33). 'Freed from 
appendants' (akiñcana) is a term for the perfectly Holy One (Arahat).

