pativedha


'penetration',  
signifies the realization of the truth of the Dhamma, as distinguished from 
the mere acquisition of its wording (pariyatti), or the practice 
(patipatti) of it, in other words, realization as distinguished from theory 
and practice. Cf. pariyatti.

