sammasana


'comprehension', exploring, 'determining' (vavatthāna,
q.v.)  
is a name for the determining of all phenomena of existence as impermanent, 
miserable and impersonal (anicca, dukkha, anattā), etc., which is the 
beginning of insight (s. Pts.M. I, p. 53; Vis.M. XX); also called kalāpa-s.
