samvejaníya







samvejanīya-tthāna


'places rousing emotion', are 4:




the place where the Perfect One was born, (i.e. the Lumbini-grove near 
Kapilavatthu, at the present frontier of Nepal);  


the place where he reached Full Enlightenment (i.e. Uruvela, the modern 
Ureli, and Buddhagayā, on the Nerañjara-river; the modern Lilanja);  


the place where he, for the first time, unveiled the Dhamma to the world 
(i.e. the deer-park at Isipatana near Benares);




the place where he entered the final Nibbāna (i.e. Kusināra). (A. IV, 118).

