vatta







vatta

  1. 'round',  
  2. 'round of rebirths'.  

(1) With reference to the dependent origination (paticcasamuppāda), 
Vis.M. XVII speaks of 3 rounds:  

  the karma round (kamma-vatta)
comprising the karma-formations and the karma process (2nd and 10th links);  
  the round of defilements (kilesa-vatta) comprising ignorance, craving 
and clinging (1st, 8th and 9th links);  
  the round of results (vipāka-vatta)
comprising consciousness, mind and corporeality, 6 bases, impression, feeling 
(3rd-7th links).  


Cf. paticcasamuppāda (diagram).

(2) round of rebirth = samsāra.

